OL,3,CUtility bills and tax hikes drive
OL,4,Cinflation higher
OL,6,FThe key question now is why the
OL,7,Frebound was bigger than expected and
OL,8,Fwhether it will last, as ITV News
OL,9,FEconomics Editor Joel Hills explains
OL,11,FAll the arrows are pointing in the
OL,12,Fwrong direction.
OL,14,FInflation rose significantly in April
OL,15,Fon every measure, as prices increased
OL,16,Fmore rapidly across the UK economy.
OL,18,FThe headline annual rate jumped to
OL,19,F3.5%, above the 3.3% economists
OL,20,Fexpected and higher than the 3.4%
OL,21,Fforecast by the Bank of England.
