OL,3,CUtility bills and tax hikes drive
OL,4,Cinflation higher
OL,6,FHe notes that prices for mobile phone
OL,7,Fand broadband contracts, restaurant
OL,8,Fmeals, vehicle excise duty, package
OL,9,Fholidays and airfares all rose more
OL,10,Fthan he forecast. Food prices also
OL,11,Fclimbed strongly.
OL,13,FThe British Retail Consortium, which
OL,14,Frepresents major supermarkets, blames
OL,15,Fthe Chancellor. The October Budget
OL,16,Fraised business costs through a higher
OL,17,Fminimum wage and an increase in
OL,18,Fnational insurance.
